Subject: rPSA-2007-0161-1 dovecot

rPath Security Advisory: 2007-0161-1
Published: 2007-08-14
Products: rPath Linux 1
Rating: Minor
Exposure Level Classification:
    Remote User Deterministic Privilege Escalation
Updated Versions:
    dovecot=/conary.rpath.com@rpl:devel//1/1.0.3-0.1-1

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2007-4211
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-1621

Description:
    Previous versions of the dovecot package are vulnerable to a
    minor privilege escalation attack in which an authenticated
    user may exploit an ACL plugin weakness to save message flags
    without having proper permissions.

